est their dependence on model assumptions. Although\nthe analysis of the full CMB spectra should be always preferred, using the\nposition of the CMB peaks and dips provide a simple and consistent method for\ncombining CMB constraints with other datasets.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 27 Nov 2007 15:20:33 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 25 Mar 2008 11:19:46 GMT"}],"update_date":"2008-11-26"}
